# First Principle

## OPIc measures communication performance, not English knowledge.

Many learners mistakenly optimize for:

- vocabulary
- grammar
- memorized answers

These are inputs.

The examination evaluates the output:

> **Can you communicate naturally and continuously under realistic conversational conditions?**

---

# Core Mechanism

Speaking is a real-time decision-making process.

The complete process can be represented as:

```text
Question
      │
      ▼
Interpret Meaning
      │
      ▼
Retrieve Relevant Memory
      │
      ▼
Organize Ideas
      │
      ▼
Generate Language
      │
      ▼
Monitor Speech
      │
      ▼
Continue Conversation
```

Failure at any stage affects overall performance.

---

# The Speaking System

Speaking consists of five interacting systems.

| System | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| Comprehension | Understand the question |
| Content | Decide what to say |
| Organization | Arrange ideas logically |
| Language Production | Produce English fluently |
| Self-Monitoring | Detect and recover from mistakes |

Improving only vocabulary improves only one component.

---

# Language Knowledge vs Speaking Ability

| Language Knowledge | Speaking Ability |
|--------------------|------------------|
| Vocabulary | Communication |
| Grammar | Organization |
| Reading | Fluency |
| Memorization | Adaptation |
| Accuracy | Interaction |

Knowing English is not identical to speaking English.

---

# Why Memorized Answers Fail

Memorization assumes:

```
One Question
      ↓
One Prepared Answer
```

Real OPIc behaves differently.

```
One Topic
      ↓
Many Question Variations
      ↓
Unexpected Follow-ups
      ↓
Adaptive Conversation
```

Therefore:

```
Prepared Script
        <
Flexible Speaking Framework
```

---

# Characteristics of an AL Speaker

An AL speaker usually demonstrates:

- continuous speech
- relevant content
- logical progression
- natural transitions
- adequate detail
- recovery after hesitation
- flexibility when questions change

Perfection is not required.

Communication is.

